 of research as well as presenting novel approaches. This hitherto unique volume presents an almost encyclopaedic account illuminating the varying dimensions of a complex area.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEconomy (Linguistics). 0aPragmatics. 4aAbkürzung. 4aPragmatik (Sprache). 4aSprachlicher Ausdruck. 4aSprachtypologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aAbbreviation.  alanguage typology.  alinguistic expressions.  apragmatics (language).1 aBaßler, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBest, Karl-Heinz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusse, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBär, Jochen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBär, Jochen A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDuke, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGardt, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreule, Albrecht, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGöpferich, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGünthner, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHabermann, Mechthild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHermanns, Fritz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJanich, Nina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKreßmann, Reiner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKunkel, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKühlmann, Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ct